    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-12T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-12T13:00:00-05:00" n="301"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.55/118: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hinkle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ciudad Trujillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-12T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 12, 1940—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>98. The Minister of Foreign Affairs today said that under authority given the
                    President by the immigration law no further visas will be granted any European
                    immigrants except those settlers coming under the Dominican Republic Settlement
                    Association’s contract.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hinkle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
